<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title>Using Interval Alarms</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="./css/guide.css" />
</head>
<body class="en">
  <main class="container">
    <h1 class="page-title">Using Interval Alarms</h1>

    <p class="lead">
      Interval alarms are useful when you want repeated alerts at regular intervals.
    </p>

    <p class="paragraph">
      They can be used for focused work sessions, break management, exercise routines, or any situation where repeated reminders are helpful.
    </p>

    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Getting Started with Interval Alarms</h2>

      <p class="paragraph">
        On the Interval Alarm screen, tap the + button at the bottom to add a new interval alarm.
      </p>

      <p class="paragraph">
        Set the title, active time, break time, number of sets, and other options. Once started, alerts will repeat according to the interval you set.
      </p>

      <div class="image-block">
        <img class="guide-image guide-image-tall" src="./images/interval/interval.jpg" alt="Add interval alarm screen example" />
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Checking the Running Status</h2>

      <p class="paragraph">
        When an interval alarm is running, its current status appears in the notification area.
      </p>

      <p class="paragraph">
        The notification shows whether you are in an active or break phase, the remaining time, and the current set information.
      </p>

      <p class="paragraph">
        You can also pause or stop the interval alarm directly from the notification.
      </p>

      <div class="image-block">
        <img class="guide-image guide-image-wide" src="./images/interval/interval2.jpg" alt="Interval alarm notification example" />
        <p class="image-caption">Check the current interval alarm status and control it directly from the notification.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Example Uses</h2>

      <ul class="list">
        <li>Splitting study time and break time</li>
        <li>Managing workout routines</li>
        <li>Setting reminders for tasks that need regular checks</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="section">
      <h2 class="section-title">Please Note</h2>

      <p class="paragraph">
        Interval alarms serve a different purpose from regular wake-up alarms, so we recommend using them according to your situation.
      </p>

      <p class="paragraph">
        For long sessions, it is convenient to check the current progress from the notification area.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</body>
</html>